# Stock logos (optional local override)

The app already shows real logos automatically via the DuckDuckGo / Google
favicon APIs, with a branded ticker tile as the final fallback. You only need
files here if you want **crisp, high-resolution** logos (recommended for the
demo).

Drop a file named after the **ticker** (SVG preferred, PNG also works). If a
file exists it takes priority over the online sources.

### Tadawul (Saudi)
`2222.svg` Saudi Aramco · `1120.svg` Al Rajhi Bank · `7010.svg` stc ·
`2010.svg` SABIC · `2082.svg` ACWA Power · `1180.svg` Saudi National Bank ·
`1211.svg` Ma'aden · `2280.svg` Almarai

### US
`AAPL.svg` Apple · `NVDA.svg` NVIDIA · `MSFT.svg` Microsoft ·
`AMZN.svg` Amazon · `GOOGL.svg` Alphabet · `META.svg` Meta ·
`TSLA.svg` Tesla · `NFLX.svg` Netflix

Tips:
- Use square, transparent logos that look good on a white tile.
- SVG is sharpest; otherwise PNG ≥ 128×128.
- No files needed to ship — the favicon fallback covers every ticker.
